cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO

This paper proposes a computational framework for parsing a single RGB image and reconstructing a 3D configuration using a stochastic grammar model. The paper focuses on computer vision and graphics, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.GR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and inference algorithms, which could fall under cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper deals with 3D layout and object detection, which could be relevant to cs.RO.
